  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Assistance for Vulnerable Typhoon-Affected Households in Leyte</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In collaboration with UNICEF, RI designed activities to ensure a healthy, safe, and dignified environment for vulnerable typhoon-affected communities in Leyte Island through the provision of clean water, sanitation infrastructure, and hygiene promotion. RI provided 5,000 water kits to families, reaching more than 25,000 individuals. RI provided all required materials, design, and technical support to vulnerable households which would allow them to build 1,647 latrines in each household.  Additionally, RI has trained 7,580 individuals, including children and women, on better hygiene practices. RI is focusing on repairing the water systems in the 32 Barangays to provide households with clean water.</narrative>
  </description>
